<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1901" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1901">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 704.5467/2.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of
                                    Switzerland</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Swiss
                                    Legation</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <dateline>
                            <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-12">undated</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram received at the Legation on November 12, 1914,
                            and copied to the Secretary of State November 14, 1914.]</p>
                        <p>Please ask the United States Government to kindly cable authorization to
                            its Embassy in Constantinople that United States representatives protect
                            in the Ottoman Empire such citizens of Switzerland as are asking for
                            such protection. This will mostly affect Swiss citizens previously under
                            the protection of Powers now at war with Turkey.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hoffman</hi>, <lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">President of Confederation.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>